<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL - GEAR SHIFT
        LEVER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Remote control housings are installed the same way as gear shift levers.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For standard and forward shifter housings, make sure the three (3) balls and tension springs are
                    in the shifter housing top bores.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure the shift block and yoke notches are aligned in the neutral position.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gear shift lever gasket on the gear shift lever mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020r2">Figure 272</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020r2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020r2" filename="../figg13/G13020R2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 272. Gear Shift Lever Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fit the gear shift lever into the shift block (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020r2">Figure 272</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller Sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020r3">Figure 273</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020r3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020r3" filename="../figg13/G13020R3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 273. Install Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
